caption: Most of the good thai food places are located in queens, well turns out I was wrong , after I've discovered To Be Thai. Nice customer service, fast and fresh food . And mouthwatering delicious taste. I've rest my case .
Give the wrong stuff
the food is very good
Best Thai Restaurant in nyc
bro the fried chicken event was poggers 100%
Love it. One of my favorite place to eat. Food is tasty. Lady at the front counter very friendly.
To Be Thai has my favorite pad se ew and my favorite panang curry anywhere. Their mock duck is particularly good, and their mango salad is wonderful. Their delivery is also crazy fast.
Value for money Thai food. Recommend
To Be Thai has been our only Thai place since 2007. They have the best mock duck salad and pad see ew

I ordered yesterday, But was very Disappointed with my order I got my son chicken and broccoli with white Rice, I was surprised that they hardly put chicken and broccoli and No Rice!! I ordered pad see and they gave me lomein?? I tired calling them back and the phone was busy, for one hour . What a bad experience. I won’t be ordering from here anymore
One of my main places to eat. convenient location, neat, and fantastic service. Keep it up!
This place has some of the best drunken noodles! Spicy and delicious!
We frequently order take out from To Be Thai and it is consistently delicious, the portions are good, and they always have the order ready quickly. Love it!
The food was very tasty...n the service is really good ...love to go there again
No meat just skin ! And small portions for overprice and Play like you were in the refrigerator for a while and then got under the heat Doesn’t taste fresh
Super friendly little local place
Best Thai food in Brooklyn.
Yum!
Good food
I totally recomend this place, Chicken Pad See Ew is very delicious. 5 stars To B Thai :)
They offer a nice variety of delicious food. I loved dining here. Staff members are always very friendly, prices are affordable and the place is always neat.
Good flavored, classic local thai food.
Great  Thai food
So so Thai taste food but good services anyway.
I love the salad and spring roll. Amazing test,,, friendly staff
Me and my daughter ate from there and we got food posioning.
Is good for Chinese food.

I have no issue with the taste of the food. I have issue with the following. First, I ordered my food at 7:30PM and did not get it until 9:00PM. I had several phone calls with the restaurant and they were very unhelpful. They kept telling me my food was on the way, the delivery guy is 5 minutes away.When the food finally came, it looked like it was dropped in a puddle. Additionally, the food was cold. We spent $60 dollars on a meal that was soaked and needed to be microwaved.
Only would come here for their lunch special. Food i would say is 7/10 i’ve had better thai food. But okay for a neighborhood restaurant.
If you want real authentic Thai food. This is where you should go!
I told my dad to get a salmon fish and rice the rice was pretty good and the vegtables on the side was good but the salmon was bad it was dry and bland and the thai sauce was disgusting
Great food great place
Good food, pleasant environment, good service.

I ordered the pad Thai, duck mango salad, the coconut soup and the Thai tea and everything was horrible. I ordered it on GrubHub but if I were sitting in I would definitely have sent it back. Worse Thai I ever had. The pad Thai was bunt and the mango salad was water? Like almost have the container was liquid which makes no sense to me. Will never recommend
The food was horrible and didn't have any flavor.. I have had much better.
Ordered takeout.  The wife loved the food.  I just had the salad.  The dressing was light and flavorful.
This place smells like dog's... I am sure they cook 🐕 no joke's.
Good food and conveniently located next to the F line
(Translated by Google) Very good food. 😋 delicious  (Original) Muy buena comida. 😋 deliciosa
Very good the food!
Pleasant service and food
Waitress were very nice to us. Food test really good and not pricey.

I agree with a previous post. Just had the pad Thai and it was disgusting,  and to be honest it made me ill. Avoid at all costs. Especially since there are plenty of other places near by that are better.

I've been here several times.  I really like the crab Rangoon, green curry, panang curry, pad see ew, Thai basil eggplant, and tom kha soup.  We recently tried the pepper steak which was bland and the peanut lover's dish, which was ok.

Great dishes and great prices! I had the fresh squid in red chile sauce, spicy. It wasn't overly spicy, but so flavorful I didn't care. My husband had the cashews and chicken with peanut sauce and this too was tasty and fabulous. Highly recommend
Really good! Noodles were on the sweet side but delicious. Basil beef-curry and a catfish dish, all had wonderful flavors
Food was delicious. Service was fast and quick. Reccomended.
Excellent food and service. I also enjoy the lively nrighborhood.
I love their basil fried rice with shrimp and beef. Their thai fried rice is also good. The place is very clean and has a good sitting space.
Pretty good Thai food
Great food. Shrimp and Vegetable tofu fried Thai rice are amazing. One or the other are a must try.
Green Curry Chicken is very good !

Great taste of green curry.. Good portion size.. Quite inexpensive.. Only problem was they didn't accept credit cards!!!! We had to pay $70 in cash. I wish she had told us when we ordered over the phone..
Remember they only take cash
The food is very good!
Great food, and polite staff.

I'm surprised about all the mixed reviews but this is my go to spot for anything Thai in the neighborhood. The food is consistently tasty and they offer quick service. In addition, when ordering through seamless they always meet the delivery ETA.  One word of caution, if you intend to eat in bring cash. While they accept credit card transactions through seamless, they don't accept credit cards in the restaurant.
Good food! Good place!
The place was recommended by friends. It's a good Thai food restaurant and they continuously get orders.
This food was tough to eat. The Pad See Ew had barely any sauce, and was just a pile of soggy noodles. The Spring Rolls were soggy and barely edible.
My favorite pad Thai and massaman curry. Yum!
Best pad Thai!
Always reliably good
Good food and a good price.
Great take out. Not a sit down restaurant
Best Thai food in Brooklyn
Great place to eat

ordered to my house description said spicy and I asked them to make sure and they said it was but it arrived and was not spicy what's so ever and the food tasted REALLY BAD . I do not recommend ! WASTE OF MONEY !!!
The food is good.price are ok as well
Good Thai food, clean, pleasant vibe.  BYOB, with beer and wine available in neighborhood.  Very affordable.
I really love that you can order extra tofu here tasty good lunch special
Nice small place with inexpensive lunch specials.  Good this food.
The food is delicious...fresh, customer service is great. We order for delivery for the first time best experience ever...thank you guys for the great lunch...
Very tasty food,  quick delivery,  decent table service,  no restroom and no alcohol served.

The food here is really great! The restaurant itself is small but it's very cute. It's cash only when you go there but you can order from seamless and pay with a card which I find inconvenient, but it's okay.  Overall, good place!
Great Thai food. Only complain is they using the wrong container for their curry. 20 to 30 minutes for take out and their lunch special is a good deal.
Good Thai food for cheap. Very small place though. If you have a large crowd, you may want to rethink. Just order on the phone. They deliver.
Here is a photograph of literally a cigarette butt that came mixed in with our order from To Be Thai. You be the judge.
We had a great time at this place. The food is your typical Thai fare but is flavorful, filling, and priced reasonably. Service was courteous and fast. Highly recommended!
Solid Americanized Thai food. Swift delivery.
Decent local Thai joint
My go to sit down cheap Thai restaurant. Decore is minimal food is cheap. People are nice
Great food. Would love to go there again of I get the chance
Pretty decent little Thai joint with fair prices, a little too greasy though
The food is great and the service is great too
One of the best Thai in the area, good food great service but it's a bit expensive

I ordered from here on seamless and the food had flavor, but tasted bad. The delivery was quick, however the food tasted cheap and the ingredients seemed like they were either overcooked and canned or overcooked and old and canned. To add a quick note - the portions are small for entrees.
decent curry chicken and the curry puffs are very good, even when delivered

We wanted to order delivery from this place but wanted to make sure if they delivered to our area since we thought it was probably to far away we called and it took like 10min of yelling in their language over the phone to finally get answered ' Yes'. We ordered simple chicken pad Thai and vegetable Thai fried Rice. It took quite a while for our food to get here but were hoping it was as good as most people claimed. The amount they give is good but we start eating it and was flavorless and looked pretty plain lacking ingredients that we usually get at most Thai restaurants. We'll just stick to our usual place.
The service was super slow, and in general the food was not as good as all these white people claim. Pretty good, but even more overrated.
Spicy!!
Loved the shrimp Tom Yum soup and the Massaman curry
Love this place. Great atmosphere, music, and best of all the people.
They have the best Thai iced coffee, definitely recommend!!
Ok food is Fine over priced for what they give you fresh taste great for the prices you should definitely get more food
My family loves it people are awesome, we  visit everytime im in from fl
Great place! Very good service and good food!
Excellent food. Good prices. Cozy place. Attentive staff. Pay them a visit if you're in the area.

Good food, great prices. The pad kee mow will keep you coming back for more (just watch out for the peppers!). Don't come here expecting candles and a romantic atmosphere. Here, it's all about serving up good quality, food without all the bells and whistles.
The food is great

Delicious! Fresh ingredients and yummy flavors! I've never been to Thailand but this place feels authentic. So far I've had the summer rolls, tom yum soup with veggies (very filling!), chicken satay and ginger sautee. All great! oh yeah and they have mango and sticky rice!! yesss

The only place I've been to in New York where the food tastes anything even remotely like it does in Thailand. The prices are quite reasonable too, especially on weekdays when they have reduced-price lunch specials. With their fast service and friendly people,To B Thai is definitely a place I would recommend. Dishes to try: Red Curry with duck and Pad Lomein Kee-Mow Noodles
Great Thai food in Kensington. Incredibly fast delivery.

BEST Spring rolls in Brooklyn. I Get some every other day! the sauce to go is so perfect. YUM I WANT SOME RIGHT NOW. The Thai fried rice, I don't love so much :( has no spice nor taste!!!! overall friendly staff and I would continue to come for the SPRING ROLLS :)
AWESOME FOOD

I like that this place is tucked away from busy Church Avenue/McDonald avenue and definitely come here when I want to dine in. They have huge portions and delicious food. But, there is sometimes a weird neighborhood guy that's standing RIGHT outside of the restaurant. With glass windows, it gets a bit awkward.
